cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the impact of user mobility on interference and outage correlation models in wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical calculations and modeling, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the impact of mobility on receiver performance, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
